 146 |     |     function read(StdStorage storage self) private returns (bytes memory) {
 147 |     |         address t = self._target;
 148 |     |         uint256 s = find(self);
 149 |     |         return abi.encode(vm.load(t, bytes32(s)));
 150 |     |     }
 151 |     | 
 152 |     |     function read_bytes32(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (bytes32) {
 153 |     |         return abi.decode(read(self), (bytes32));
 154 |     |     }
 155 |     | 
 156 |     |     function read_bool(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (bool) {
 157 |     |         int256 v = read_int(self);
 158 |     |         if (v == 0) return false;
 159 |     |         if (v == 1) return true;
 160 |     |         revert("stdStorage read_bool(StdStorage): Cannot decode. Make sure you are reading a bool.");
 161 |     |     }
 162 |     | 
 163 |     |     function read_address(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (address) {
 164 |     |         return abi.decode(read(self), (address));
 165 |     |     }
 166 |     | 
 167 |     |     function read_uint(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (uint256) {
 168 |     |         return abi.decode(read(self), (uint256));
 169 |     |     }
 170 |     | 
 171 |     |     function read_int(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (int256) {
 172 |     |         return abi.decode(read(self), (int256));
 173 |     |     }
 174 |     | 
 175 |     |     function parent(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (uint256, bytes32) {
 176 |     |         address who = self._target;
 177 |     |         uint256 field_depth = self._depth;
 178 |     |         vm.startMappingRecording();
 179 |     |         uint256 child = find(self) - field_depth;
 180 |     |         (bool found, bytes32 key, bytes32 parent_slot) = vm.getMappingKeyAndParentOf(who, bytes32(child));
 181 |     |         if (!found) {
 182 |     |             revert(
 183 |     |                 "stdStorage read_bool(StdStorage): Cannot find parent. Make sure you give a slot and startMappingRecording() has been called."
 184 |     |             );
 185 |     |         }
 186 |     |         return (uint256(parent_slot), key);
 187 |     |     }
 188 |     | 
 189 |     |     function root(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (uint256) {
 190 |     |         address who = self._target;
 191 |     |         uint256 field_depth = self._depth;
 192 |     |         vm.startMappingRecording();
 193 |     |         uint256 child = find(self) - field_depth;
 194 |     |         bool found;
 195 |     |         bytes32 root_slot;
 196 |     |         bytes32 parent_slot;
 197 |     |         (found,, parent_slot) = vm.getMappingKeyAndParentOf(who, bytes32(child));
 198 |     |         if (!found) {
 199 |     |             revert(
 200 |     |                 "stdStorage read_bool(StdStorage): Cannot find parent. Make sure you give a slot and startMappingRecording() has been called."
 201 |     |             );
 202 |     |         }
 203 |     |         while (found) {
 204 |     |             root_slot = parent_slot;
 205 |     |             (found,, parent_slot) = vm.getMappingKeyAndParentOf(who, bytes32(root_slot));
 206 |     |         }
 207 |     |         return uint256(root_slot);
 208 |     |     }
 209 |     | 
 210 |     |     function bytesToBytes32(bytes memory b, uint256 offset) private pure returns (bytes32) {
 211 |     |         bytes32 out;
 212 |     | 
 213 |     |         uint256 max = b.length > 32 ? 32 : b.length;
 214 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < max; i++) {
 215 |     |             out |= bytes32(b[offset + i] & 0xFF) >> (i * 8);
 216 |     |         }
 217 |     |         return out;
 218 |     |     }
 219 |     | 
 220 |     |     function flatten(bytes32[] memory b) private pure returns (bytes memory) {
 221 |     |         bytes memory result = new bytes(b.length * 32);
 222 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < b.length; i++) {
 223 |     |             bytes32 k = b[i];
 224 |     |             /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
 225 |     |             assembly {
 226 |     |                 mstore(add(result, add(32, mul(32, i))), k)
 227 |     |             }
 228 |     |         }
 229 |     | 
 230 |     |         return result;
 231 |     |     }
 232 |     | }

 275 |     |     }

 278 |     |         checked_write(self, bytes32(amt));
 279 |     |     }

 281 |     |     function checked_write_int(StdStorage storage self, int256 val) internal {
 282 |     |         checked_write(self, bytes32(uint256(val)));
 283 |     |     }
 284 |     | 
 285 |     |     function checked_write(StdStorage storage self, bool write) internal {
 286 |     |         bytes32 t;
 287 |     |         /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
 288 |     |         assembly {
 289 |     |             t := write
 290 |     |         }
 291 |     |         checked_write(self, t);
 292 |     |     }
 293 |     | 
 294 |     |     function checked_write(StdStorage storage self, bytes32 set) internal {
 295 |     |         address who = self._target;
 296 |     |         bytes4 fsig = self._sig;
 297 |     |         uint256 field_depth = self._depth;
 298 |     |         bytes32[] memory ins = self._keys;
 299 |     | 
 300 |     |         bytes memory cald = abi.encodePacked(fsig, flatten(ins));
 301 |     |         if (!self.finds[who][fsig][keccak256(abi.encodePacked(ins, field_depth))]) {
 302 |     |             find(self);
 303 |     |         }
 304 |     |         bytes32 slot = bytes32(self.slots[who][fsig][keccak256(abi.encodePacked(ins, field_depth))]);
 305 |     | 
 306 |     |         bytes32 fdat;
 307 |     |         {
 308 |     |             (, bytes memory rdat) = who.staticcall(cald);
 309 |     |             fdat = bytesToBytes32(rdat, 32 * field_depth);
 310 |     |         }
 311 |     |         bytes32 curr = vm.load(who, slot);
 312 |     | 
 313 |     |         if (fdat != curr) {
 314 |     |             require(
 315 |     |                 false,
 316 |     |                 "stdStorage find(StdStorage): Packed slot. This would cause dangerous overwriting and currently isn't supported."
 317 |     |             );
 318 |     |         }
 319 |     |         vm.store(who, slot, set);
 320 |     |         delete self._target;
 321 |     |         delete self._sig;
 322 |     |         delete self._keys;
 323 |     |         delete self._depth;
 324 |     |     }
 325 |     | 
 326 |     |     function read_bytes32(StdStorage storage self) internal returns (bytes32) {
 327 |     |         return stdStorageSafe.read_bytes32(self);
 328 |     |     }

 331 |     |         return stdStorageSafe.read_bool(self);
 332 |     |     }

 335 |     |         return stdStorageSafe.read_address(self);
 336 |     |     }

 339 |     |         return stdStorageSafe.read_uint(self);
 340 |     |     }

 354 |     |     // Private function so needs to be copied over
 355 |     |     function bytesToBytes32(bytes memory b, uint256 offset) private pure returns (bytes32) {
 356 |     |         bytes32 out;
 357 |     | 
 358 |     |         uint256 max = b.length > 32 ? 32 : b.length;
 359 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < max; i++) {
 360 |     |             out |= bytes32(b[offset + i] & 0xFF) >> (i * 8);
 361 |     |         }
 362 |     |         return out;
 363 |     |     }
 364 |     | 
 365 |     |     // Private function so needs to be copied over
 366 |     |     function flatten(bytes32[] memory b) private pure returns (bytes memory) {
 367 |     |         bytes memory result = new bytes(b.length * 32);
 368 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < b.length; i++) {
 369 |     |             bytes32 k = b[i];
 370 |     |             /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
 371 |     |             assembly {
 372 |     |                 mstore(add(result, add(32, mul(32, i))), k)
 373 |     |             }
 374 |     |         }
 375 |     | 
 376 |     |         return result;
 377 |     |     }

/Users/elvisskozdopolj/Documents/TOB/echidna-auto-poc/test/lib/forge-std/src/StdUtils.sol
   1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
   2 |     | pragma solidity >=0.6.2 <0.9.0;
   3 |     | 
   4 |     | pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;
   5 |     | 
   6 |     | import {IMulticall3} from "./interfaces/IMulticall3.sol";
   7 |     | import {MockERC20} from "./mocks/MockERC20.sol";
   8 |     | import {MockERC721} from "./mocks/MockERC721.sol";
   9 |     | import {VmSafe} from "./Vm.sol";
  10 |     | 
  11 |     | abstract contract StdUtils {
  12 |     |     /*//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
  13 |     |                                      CONSTANTS
  14 |     |     //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////*/
  15 |     | 
  16 |     |     IMulticall3 private constant multicall = IMulticall3(0xcA11bde05977b3631167028862bE2a173976CA11);
  17 |     |     VmSafe private constant vm = VmSafe(address(uint160(uint256(keccak256("hevm cheat code")))));
  18 |     |     address private constant CONSOLE2_ADDRESS = 0x000000000000000000636F6e736F6c652e6c6f67;
  19 |     |     uint256 private constant INT256_MIN_ABS =
  20 |     |         57896044618658097711785492504343953926634992332820282019728792003956564819968;
  21 |     |     uint256 private constant SECP256K1_ORDER =
  22 |     |         115792089237316195423570985008687907852837564279074904382605163141518161494337;
  23 |     |     uint256 private constant UINT256_MAX =
  24 |     |         115792089237316195423570985008687907853269984665640564039457584007913129639935;
  25 |     | 
  26 |     |     // Used by default when deploying with create2, https://github.com/Arachnid/deterministic-deployment-proxy.
  27 |     |     address private constant CREATE2_FACTORY = 0x4e59b44847b379578588920cA78FbF26c0B4956C;
  28 |     | 
  29 |     |     /*//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
  30 |     |                                  INTERNAL FUNCTIONS
  31 |     |     //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////*/
  32 |     | 
  33 |     |     function _bound(uint256 x, uint256 min, uint256 max) internal pure virtual returns (uint256 result) {
  34 |     |         require(min <= max, "StdUtils bound(uint256,uint256,uint256): Max is less than min.");
  35 |     |         // If x is between min and max, return x directly. This is to ensure that dictionary values
  36 |     |         // do not get shifted if the min is nonzero. More info: https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std/issues/188
  37 |     |         if (x >= min && x <= max) return x;
  38 |     | 
  39 |     |         uint256 size = max - min + 1;
  40 |     | 
  41 |     |         // If the value is 0, 1, 2, 3, wrap that to min, min+1, min+2, min+3. Similarly for the UINT256_MAX side.
  42 |     |         // This helps ensure coverage of the min/max values.
  43 |     |         if (x <= 3 && size > x) return min + x;
  44 |     |         if (x >= UINT256_MAX - 3 && size > UINT256_MAX - x) return max - (UINT256_MAX - x);
  45 |     | 
  46 |     |         // Otherwise, wrap x into the range [min, max], i.e. the range is inclusive.
  47 |     |         if (x > max) {
  48 |     |             uint256 diff = x - max;
  49 |     |             uint256 rem = diff % size;
  50 |     |             if (rem == 0) return max;
  51 |     |             result = min + rem - 1;
  52 |     |         } else if (x < min) {
  53 |     |             uint256 diff = min - x;
  54 |     |             uint256 rem = diff % size;
  55 |     |             if (rem == 0) return min;
  56 |     |             result = max - rem + 1;
  57 |     |         }
  58 |     |     }
  59 |     | 
  60 |     |     function bound(uint256 x, uint256 min, uint256 max) internal pure virtual returns (uint256 result) {
  61 |     |         result = _bound(x, min, max);
  62 |     |         console2_log_StdUtils("Bound Result", result);
  63 |     |     }
  64 |     | 
  65 |     |     function _bound(int256 x, int256 min, int256 max) internal pure virtual returns (int256 result) {
  66 |     |         require(min <= max, "StdUtils bound(int256,int256,int256): Max is less than min.");
  67 |     | 
  68 |     |         // Shifting all int256 values to uint256 to use _bound function. The range of two types are:
  69 |     |         // int256 : -(2**255) ~ (2**255 - 1)
  70 |     |         // uint256:     0     ~ (2**256 - 1)
  71 |     |         // So, add 2**255, INT256_MIN_ABS to the integer values.
  72 |     |         //
  73 |     |         // If the given integer value is -2**255, we cannot use `-uint256(-x)` because of the overflow.
  74 |     |         // So, use `~uint256(x) + 1` instead.
  75 |     |         uint256 _x = x < 0 ? (INT256_MIN_ABS - ~uint256(x) - 1) : (uint256(x) + INT256_MIN_ABS);
  76 |     |         uint256 _min = min < 0 ? (INT256_MIN_ABS - ~uint256(min) - 1) : (uint256(min) + INT256_MIN_ABS);
  77 |     |         uint256 _max = max < 0 ? (INT256_MIN_ABS - ~uint256(max) - 1) : (uint256(max) + INT256_MIN_ABS);
  78 |     | 
  79 |     |         uint256 y = _bound(_x, _min, _max);
  80 |     | 
  81 |     |         // To move it back to int256 value, subtract INT256_MIN_ABS at here.
  82 |     |         result = y < INT256_MIN_ABS ? int256(~(INT256_MIN_ABS - y) + 1) : int256(y - INT256_MIN_ABS);
  83 |     |     }
  84 |     | 
  85 |     |     function bound(int256 x, int256 min, int256 max) internal pure virtual returns (int256 result) {
  86 |     |         result = _bound(x, min, max);
  87 |     |         console2_log_StdUtils("Bound result", vm.toString(result));
  88 |     |     }
  89 |     | 
  90 |     |     function boundPrivateKey(uint256 privateKey) internal pure virtual returns (uint256 result) {
  91 |     |         result = _bound(privateKey, 1, SECP256K1_ORDER - 1);
  92 |     |     }
  93 |     | 
  94 |     |     function bytesToUint(bytes memory b) internal pure virtual returns (uint256) {
  95 |     |         require(b.length <= 32, "StdUtils bytesToUint(bytes): Bytes length exceeds 32.");
  96 |     |         return abi.decode(abi.encodePacked(new bytes(32 - b.length), b), (uint256));
  97 |     |     }
  98 |     | 
  99 |     |     /// @dev Compute the address a contract will be deployed at for a given deployer address and nonce
 100 |     |     /// @notice adapted from Solmate implementation (https://github.com/Rari-Capital/solmate/blob/main/src/utils/LibRLP.sol)
 101 |     |     function computeCreateAddress(address deployer, uint256 nonce) internal pure virtual returns (address) {
 102 |     |         console2_log_StdUtils("computeCreateAddress is deprecated. Please use vm.computeCreateAddress instead.");
 103 |     |         return vm.computeCreateAddress(deployer, nonce);
 104 |     |     }
 105 |     |

 109 |     |         virtual

 112 |     |         console2_log_StdUtils("computeCreate2Address is deprecated. Please use vm.computeCreate2Address instead.");
 113 |     |         return vm.computeCreate2Address(salt, initcodeHash, deployer);
 114 |     |     }

 137 |     |     /// @dev returns the hash of the init code (creation code + no args) used in CREATE2 with no constructor arguments
 138 |     |     /// @param creationCode the creation code of a contract C, as returned by type(C).creationCode
 139 |     |     function hashInitCode(bytes memory creationCode) internal pure returns (bytes32) {
 140 |     |         return hashInitCode(creationCode, "");
 141 |     |     }
 142 |     | 
 143 |     |     /// @dev returns the hash of the init code (creation code + ABI-encoded args) used in CREATE2
 144 |     |     /// @param creationCode the creation code of a contract C, as returned by type(C).creationCode
 145 |     |     /// @param args the ABI-encoded arguments to the constructor of C
 146 |     |     function hashInitCode(bytes memory creationCode, bytes memory args) internal pure returns (bytes32) {
 147 |     |         return keccak256(abi.encodePacked(creationCode, args));
 148 |     |     }
 149 |     | 
 150 |     |     // Performs a single call with Multicall3 to query the ERC-20 token balances of the given addresses.
 151 |     |     function getTokenBalances(address token, address[] memory addresses)
 152 |     |         internal
 153 |     |         virtual
 154 |     |         returns (uint256[] memory balances)
 155 |     |     {
 156 |     |         uint256 tokenCodeSize;
 157 |     |         assembly {
 158 |     |             tokenCodeSize := extcodesize(token)
 159 |     |         }
 160 |     |         require(tokenCodeSize > 0, "StdUtils getTokenBalances(address,address[]): Token address is not a contract.");
 161 |     | 
 162 |     |         // ABI encode the aggregate call to Multicall3.
 163 |     |         uint256 length = addresses.length;
 164 |     |         IMulticall3.Call[] memory calls = new IMulticall3.Call[](length);
 165 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
 166 |     |             // 0x70a08231 = bytes4("balanceOf(address)"))
 167 |     |             calls[i] = IMulticall3.Call({target: token, callData: abi.encodeWithSelector(0x70a08231, (addresses[i]))});
 168 |     |         }
 169 |     | 
 170 |     |         // Make the aggregate call.
 171 |     |         (, bytes[] memory returnData) = multicall.aggregate(calls);
 172 |     | 
 173 |     |         // ABI decode the return data and return the balances.
 174 |     |         balances = new uint256[](length);
 175 |     |         for (uint256 i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
 176 |     |             balances[i] = abi.decode(returnData[i], (uint256));
 177 |     |         }
 178 |     |     }
 179 |     | 
 180 |     |     /*//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
 181 |     |                                  PRIVATE FUNCTIONS
 182 |     |     //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////*/
 183 |     | 
 184 |     |     function addressFromLast20Bytes(bytes32 bytesValue) private pure returns (address) {
 185 |     |         return address(uint160(uint256(bytesValue)));
 186 |     |     }
 187 |     | 
 188 |     |     // This section is used to prevent the compilation of console, which shortens the compilation time when console is
 189 |     |     // not used elsewhere. We also trick the compiler into letting us make the console log methods as `pure` to avoid
 190 |     |     // any breaking changes to function signatures.
 191 |     |     function _castLogPayloadViewToPure(function(bytes memory) internal view fnIn)
 192 |     |         internal
 193 |     |         pure
 194 |     |         returns (function(bytes memory) internal pure fnOut)
 195 |     |     {
 196 |     |         assembly {
 197 |     |             fnOut := fnIn
 198 |     |         }
 199 |     |     }
 200 |     | 
 201 |     |     function _sendLogPayload(bytes memory payload) internal pure {
 202 |     |         _castLogPayloadViewToPure(_sendLogPayloadView)(payload);
 203 |     |     }
 204 |     | 
 205 |     |     function _sendLogPayloadView(bytes memory payload) private view {
 206 |     |         uint256 payloadLength = payload.length;
 207 |     |         address consoleAddress = CONSOLE2_ADDRESS;
 208 |     |         /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
 209 |     |         assembly {
 210 |     |             let payloadStart := add(payload, 32)
 211 |     |             let r := staticcall(gas(), consoleAddress, payloadStart, payloadLength, 0, 0)
 212 |     |         }
 213 |     |     }
 214 |     | 
 215 |     |     function console2_log_StdUtils(string memory p0) private pure {
 216 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(string)", p0));
 217 |     |     }
 218 |     | 
 219 |     |     function console2_log_StdUtils(string memory p0, uint256 p1) private pure {
 220 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(string,uint256)", p0, p1));
 221 |     |     }
 222 |     | 
 223 |     |     function console2_log_StdUtils(string memory p0, string memory p1) private pure {
 224 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(string,string)", p0, p1));
 225 |     |     }
 226 |     | }

/Users/elvisskozdopolj/Documents/TOB/echidna-auto-poc/test/lib/forge-std/src/Vm.sol
   1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
   2 |     | pragma solidity >=0.6.2 <0.9.0;
   3 |     | 
   4 |     | pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;
   5 |     | 
   6 |     | // Cheatcodes are marked as view/pure/none using the following rules:
   7 |     | // 0. A call's observable behaviour includes its return value, logs, reverts and state writes,
   8 |     | // 1. If you can influence a later call's observable behaviour, you're neither `view` nor `pure (you are modifying some state be it the EVM, interpreter, filesystem, etc),
   9 |     | // 2. Otherwise if you can be influenced by an earlier call, or if reading some state, you're `view`,
  10 |     | // 3. Otherwise you're `pure`.
  11 |     | 
  12 |     | // The `VmSafe` interface does not allow manipulation of the EVM state or other actions that may
  13 |     | // result in Script simulations differing from on-chain execution. It is recommended to only use
  14 |     | // these cheats in scripts.
  15 |     | interface VmSafe {
  16 |     |     //  ======== Types ========
  17 |     |     enum CallerMode {
  18 |     |         None,
  19 |     |         Broadcast,
  20 |     |         RecurrentBroadcast,
  21 |     |         Prank,
  22 |     |         RecurrentPrank
  23 |     |     }
  24 |     | 
  25 |     |     enum AccountAccessKind {
  26 |     |         Call,
  27 |     |         DelegateCall,
  28 |     |         CallCode,
  29 |     |         StaticCall,
  30 |     |         Create,
  31 |     |         SelfDestruct,
  32 |     |         Resume,
  33 |     |         Balance,
  34 |     |         Extcodesize,
  35 |     |         Extcodehash,
  36 |     |         Extcodecopy
  37 |     |     }
  38 |     | 
  39 |     |     struct Log {
  40 |     |         bytes32[] topics;
  41 |     |         bytes data;
  42 |     |         address emitter;
  43 |     |     }
  44 |     | 
  45 |     |     struct Rpc {
  46 |     |         string key;
  47 |     |         string url;
  48 |     |     }
  49 |     | 
  50 |     |     struct EthGetLogs {
  51 |     |         address emitter;
  52 |     |         bytes32[] topics;
  53 |     |         bytes data;
  54 |     |         bytes32 blockHash;
  55 |     |         uint64 blockNumber;
  56 |     |         bytes32 transactionHash;
  57 |     |         uint64 transactionIndex;
  58 |     |         uint256 logIndex;
  59 |     |         bool removed;
  60 |     |     }
  61 |     | 
  62 |     |     struct DirEntry {
  63 |     |         string errorMessage;
  64 |     |         string path;
  65 |     |         uint64 depth;
  66 |     |         bool isDir;
  67 |     |         bool isSymlink;
  68 |     |     }
  69 |     | 
  70 |     |     struct FsMetadata {
  71 |     |         bool isDir;
  72 |     |         bool isSymlink;
  73 |     |         uint256 length;
  74 |     |         bool readOnly;
  75 |     |         uint256 modified;
  76 |     |         uint256 accessed;
  77 |     |         uint256 created;
  78 |     |     }
  79 |     | 
  80 |     |     struct Wallet {
  81 |     |         address addr;
  82 |     |         uint256 publicKeyX;
  83 |     |         uint256 publicKeyY;
  84 |     |         uint256 privateKey;
  85 |     |     }
  86 |     | 
  87 |     |     struct FfiResult {
  88 |     |         int32 exitCode;
  89 |     |         bytes stdout;
  90 |     |         bytes stderr;
  91 |     |     }
  92 |     | 
  93 |     |     struct ChainInfo {
  94 |     |         uint256 forkId;
  95 |     |         uint256 chainId;
  96 |     |     }
  97 |     | 
  98 |     |     struct AccountAccess {
  99 |     |         ChainInfo chainInfo;
 100 |     |         AccountAccessKind kind;
 101 |     |         address account;
 102 |     |         address accessor;
 103 |     |         bool initialized;
 104 |     |         uint256 oldBalance;
 105 |     |         uint256 newBalance;
 106 |     |         bytes deployedCode;
 107 |     |         uint256 value;
 108 |     |         bytes data;
 109 |     |         bool reverted;
 110 |     |         StorageAccess[] storageAccesses;
 111 |     |     }
 112 |     | 
 113 |     |     struct StorageAccess {
 114 |     |         address account;
 115 |     |         bytes32 slot;
 116 |     |         bool isWrite;
 117 |     |         bytes32 previousValue;
 118 |     |         bytes32 newValue;
 119 |     |         bool reverted;
 120 |     |     }
 121 |     | 
 122 |     |     // ======== EVM  ========
 123 |     | 
 124 |     |     // Gets the address for a given private key
 125 |     |     function addr(uint256 privateKey) external pure returns (address keyAddr);
 126 |     | 
 127 |     |     // Gets the nonce of an account.
 128 |     |     // See `getNonce(Wallet memory wallet)` for an alternative way to manage users and get their nonces.
 129 |     |     function getNonce(address account) external view returns (uint64 nonce);
 130 |     | 
 131 |     |     // Loads a storage slot from an address
 132 |     |     function load(address target, bytes32 slot) external view returns (bytes32 data);
 133 |     | 
 134 |     |     // Signs data
 135 |     |     function sign(uint256 privateKey, bytes32 digest) external pure returns (uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s);
 136 |     | 
 137 |     |     // -------- Record Storage --------
 138 |     |     // Records all storage reads and writes
 139 |     |     function record() external;
 140 |     | 
 141 |     |     // Gets all accessed reads and write slot from a `vm.record` session, for a given address
 142 |     |     function accesses(address target) external returns (bytes32[] memory readSlots, bytes32[] memory writeSlots);
 143 |     | 
 144 |     |     // Record all account accesses as part of CREATE, CALL or SELFDESTRUCT opcodes in order,
 145 |     |     // along with the context of the calls.
 146 |     |     function startStateDiffRecording() external;
 147 |     | 
 148 |     |     // Returns an ordered array of all account accesses from a `vm.startStateDiffRecording` session.
 149 |     |     function stopAndReturnStateDiff() external returns (AccountAccess[] memory accountAccesses);
 150 |     | 
 151 |     |     // -------- Recording Map Writes --------
 152 |     | 
 153 |     |     // Starts recording all map SSTOREs for later retrieval.
 154 |     |     function startMappingRecording() external;
 155 |     | 
 156 |     |     // Stops recording all map SSTOREs for later retrieval and clears the recorded data.
 157 |     |     function stopMappingRecording() external;
 158 |     |

 160 |     |     function getMappingLength(address target, bytes32 mappingSlot) external returns (uint256 length);
 161 |     | 
 162 |     |     // Gets the elements at index idx of the mapping at the given slot, for a given address. The
 163 |     |     // index must be less than the length of the mapping (i.e. the number of keys in the mapping).
 164 |     |     function getMappingSlotAt(address target, bytes32 mappingSlot, uint256 idx) external returns (bytes32 value);
 165 |     |

 167 |     |     function getMappingKeyAndParentOf(address target, bytes32 elementSlot)
 168 |     |         external
 169 |     |         returns (bool found, bytes32 key, bytes32 parent);

 243 |     |     // -------- Reading and writing --------
 244 |     | 
 245 |     |     // Closes file for reading, resetting the offset and allowing to read it from beginning with readLine.
 246 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 247 |     |     function closeFile(string calldata path) external;
 248 |     | 
 249 |     |     // Copies the contents of one file to another. This function will **overwrite** the contents of `to`.
 250 |     |     // On success, the total number of bytes copied is returned and it is equal to the length of the `to` file as reported by `metadata`.
 251 |     |     // Both `from` and `to` are relative to the project root.
 252 |     |     function copyFile(string calldata from, string calldata to) external returns (uint64 copied);
 253 |     | 
 254 |     |     // Creates a new, empty directory at the provided path.
 255 |     |     // This cheatcode will revert in the following situations, but is not limited to just these cases:
 256 |     |     // - User lacks permissions to modify `path`.
 257 |     |     // - A parent of the given path doesn't exist and `recursive` is false.
 258 |     |     // - `path` already exists and `recursive` is false.
 259 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 260 |     |     function createDir(string calldata path, bool recursive) external;
 261 |     | 
 262 |     |     // Reads the directory at the given path recursively, up to `max_depth`.
 263 |     |     // `max_depth` defaults to 1, meaning only the direct children of the given directory will be returned.
 264 |     |     // Follows symbolic links if `follow_links` is true.
 265 |     |     function readDir(string calldata path) external view returns (DirEntry[] memory entries);
 266 |     |     function readDir(string calldata path, uint64 maxDepth) external view returns (DirEntry[] memory entries);
 267 |     |     function readDir(string calldata path, uint64 maxDepth, bool followLinks)
 268 |     |         external
 269 |     |         view
 270 |     |         returns (DirEntry[] memory entries);
 271 |     | 
 272 |     |     // Reads the entire content of file to string. `path` is relative to the project root.
 273 |     |     function readFile(string calldata path) external view returns (string memory data);
 274 |     | 
 275 |     |     // Reads the entire content of file as binary. `path` is relative to the project root.
 276 |     |     function readFileBinary(string calldata path) external view returns (bytes memory data);
 277 |     | 
 278 |     |     // Reads next line of file to string.
 279 |     |     function readLine(string calldata path) external view returns (string memory line);
 280 |     | 
 281 |     |     // Reads a symbolic link, returning the path that the link points to.
 282 |     |     // This cheatcode will revert in the following situations, but is not limited to just these cases:
 283 |     |     // - `path` is not a symbolic link.
 284 |     |     // - `path` does not exist.
 285 |     |     function readLink(string calldata linkPath) external view returns (string memory targetPath);
 286 |     | 
 287 |     |     // Removes a directory at the provided path.
 288 |     |     // This cheatcode will revert in the following situations, but is not limited to just these cases:
 289 |     |     // - `path` doesn't exist.
 290 |     |     // - `path` isn't a directory.
 291 |     |     // - User lacks permissions to modify `path`.
 292 |     |     // - The directory is not empty and `recursive` is false.
 293 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 294 |     |     function removeDir(string calldata path, bool recursive) external;
 295 |     | 
 296 |     |     // Removes a file from the filesystem.
 297 |     |     // This cheatcode will revert in the following situations, but is not limited to just these cases:
 298 |     |     // - `path` points to a directory.
 299 |     |     // - The file doesn't exist.
 300 |     |     // - The user lacks permissions to remove the file.
 301 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 302 |     |     function removeFile(string calldata path) external;
 303 |     | 
 304 |     |     // Writes data to file, creating a file if it does not exist, and entirely replacing its contents if it does.
 305 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 306 |     |     function writeFile(string calldata path, string calldata data) external;
 307 |     | 
 308 |     |     // Writes binary data to a file, creating a file if it does not exist, and entirely replacing its contents if it does.
 309 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 310 |     |     function writeFileBinary(string calldata path, bytes calldata data) external;
 311 |     | 
 312 |     |     // Writes line to file, creating a file if it does not exist.
 313 |     |     // `path` is relative to the project root.
 314 |     |     function writeLine(string calldata path, string calldata data) external;

 479 |     |     // ======== JSON Parsing and Manipulation ========
 480 |     | 
 481 |     |     // -------- Reading --------
 482 |     | 
 483 |     |     // NOTE: Please read https://book.getfoundry.sh/cheatcodes/parse-json to understand the
 484 |     |     // limitations and caveats of the JSON parsing cheats.
 485 |     | 
 486 |     |     // Checks if a key exists in a JSON object.
 487 |     |     function keyExists(string calldata json, string calldata key) external view returns (bool);
 488 |     | 
 489 |     |     // Given a string of JSON, return it as ABI-encoded
 490 |     |     function parseJson(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bytes memory abiEncodedData);
 491 |     |     function parseJson(string calldata json) external pure returns (bytes memory abiEncodedData);
 492 |     | 
 493 |     |     // The following parseJson cheatcodes will do type coercion, for the type that they indicate.
 494 |     |     // For example, parseJsonUint will coerce all values to a uint256. That includes stringified numbers '12'
 495 |     |     // and hex numbers '0xEF'.
 496 |     |     // Type coercion works ONLY for discrete values or arrays. That means that the key must return a value or array, not
 497 |     |     // a JSON object.
 498 |     |     function parseJsonUint(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (uint256);
 499 |     |     function parseJsonUintArray(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (uint256[] memory);
 500 |     |     function parseJsonInt(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (int256);
 501 |     |     function parseJsonIntArray(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (int256[] memory);
 502 |     |     function parseJsonBool(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bool);
 503 |     |     function parseJsonBoolArray(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bool[] memory);
 504 |     |     function parseJsonAddress(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (address);
 505 |     |     function parseJsonAddressArray(string calldata json, string calldata key)
 506 |     |         external
 507 |     |         pure
 508 |     |         returns (address[] memory);
 509 |     |     function parseJsonString(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (string memory);
 510 |     |     function parseJsonStringArray(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (string[] memory);
 511 |     |     function parseJsonBytes(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bytes memory);
 512 |     |     function parseJsonBytesArray(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bytes[] memory);
 513 |     |     function parseJsonBytes32(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (bytes32);
 514 |     |     function parseJsonBytes32Array(string calldata json, string calldata key)
 515 |     |         external
 516 |     |         pure
 517 |     |         returns (bytes32[] memory);
 518 |     | 
 519 |     |     // Returns array of keys for a JSON object
 520 |     |     function parseJsonKeys(string calldata json, string calldata key) external pure returns (string[] memory keys);
 521 |     | 
 522 |     |     // -------- Writing --------
 523 |     |

 525 |     |     // to use the serialization cheats.

 528 |     |     // It returns the stringified version of the specific JSON file up to that moment.

 540 |     |         external

 543 |     |         external

 546 |     |         external

 559 |     |         external

 562 |     |         external

 574 |     |     // NOTE: Please read https://book.getfoundry.sh/cheatcodes/write-json to understand how
 575 |     |     // to use the JSON writing cheats.
 576 |     | 
 577 |     |     // Write a serialized JSON object to a file. If the file exists, it will be overwritten.
 578 |     |     function writeJson(string calldata json, string calldata path) external;
 579 |     | 
 580 |     |     // Write a serialized JSON object to an **existing** JSON file, replacing a value with key = <value_key>
 581 |     |     // This is useful to replace a specific value of a JSON file, without having to parse the entire thing
 582 |     |     function writeJson(string calldata json, string calldata path, string calldata valueKey) external;
 583 |     | }
 584 |     | 
 585 |     | // The `Vm` interface does allow manipulation of the EVM state. These are all intended to be used
 586 |     | // in tests, but it is not recommended to use these cheats in scripts.
 587 |     | interface Vm is VmSafe {
 588 |     |     // ======== EVM  ========
 589 |     | 
 590 |     |     // -------- Block and Transaction Properties --------
 591 |     | 
 592 |     |     // Sets block.chainid
 593 |     |     function chainId(uint256 newChainId) external;
 594 |     | 
 595 |     |     // Sets block.coinbase
 596 |     |     function coinbase(address newCoinbase) external;
 597 |     | 
 598 |     |     // Sets block.difficulty
 599 |     |     // Not available on EVM versions from Paris onwards. Use `prevrandao` instead.
 600 |     |     // If used on unsupported EVM versions it will revert.
 601 |     |     function difficulty(uint256 newDifficulty) external;
 602 |     | 
 603 |     |     // Sets block.basefee
 604 |     |     function fee(uint256 newBasefee) external;
 605 |     | 
 606 |     |     // Sets block.prevrandao
 607 |     |     // Not available on EVM versions before Paris. Use `difficulty` instead.
 608 |     |     // If used on unsupported EVM versions it will revert.
 609 |     |     function prevrandao(bytes32 newPrevrandao) external;
 610 |     | 
 611 |     |     // Sets block.height
 612 |     |     function roll(uint256 newHeight) external;
 613 |     | 
 614 |     |     // Sets tx.gasprice
 615 |     |     function txGasPrice(uint256 newGasPrice) external;
 616 |     | 
 617 |     |     // Sets block.timestamp
 618 |     |     function warp(uint256 newTimestamp) external;

 620 |     |     // -------- Account State --------
 621 |     | 
 622 |     |     // Sets an address' balance
 623 |     |     function deal(address account, uint256 newBalance) external;
 624 |     | 
 625 |     |     // Sets an address' code
 626 |     |     function etch(address target, bytes calldata newRuntimeBytecode) external;
 627 |     | 
 628 |     |     // Load a genesis JSON file's `allocs` into the in-memory state.
 629 |     |     function loadAllocs(string calldata pathToAllocsJson) external;
 630 |     | 
 631 |     |     // Resets the nonce of an account to 0 for EOAs and 1 for contract accounts
 632 |     |     function resetNonce(address account) external;
 633 |     | 
 634 |     |     // Sets the nonce of an account; must be higher than the current nonce of the account
 635 |     |     function setNonce(address account, uint64 newNonce) external;
 636 |     | 
 637 |     |     // Sets the nonce of an account to an arbitrary value
 638 |     |     function setNonceUnsafe(address account, uint64 newNonce) external;
 639 |     | 
 640 |     |     // Stores a value to an address' storage slot.

 642 |     | 
 643 |     |     // -------- Call Manipulation --------
 644 |     |     // --- Mocks ---
 645 |     | 
 646 |     |     // Clears all mocked calls
 647 |     |     function clearMockedCalls() external;
 648 |     | 
 649 |     |     // Mocks a call to an address, returning specified data.
 650 |     |     // Calldata can either be strict or a partial match, e.g. if you only
 651 |     |     // pass a Solidity selector to the expected calldata, then the entire Solidity
 652 |     |     // function will be mocked.
 653 |     |     function mockCall(address callee, bytes calldata data, bytes calldata returnData) external;
 654 |     | 
 655 |     |     // Mocks a call to an address with a specific msg.value, returning specified data.
 656 |     |     // Calldata match takes precedence over msg.value in case of ambiguity.
 657 |     |     function mockCall(address callee, uint256 msgValue, bytes calldata data, bytes calldata returnData) external;
 658 |     | 
 659 |     |     // Reverts a call to an address with specified revert data.
 660 |     |     function mockCallRevert(address callee, bytes calldata data, bytes calldata revertData) external;
 661 |     | 
 662 |     |     // Reverts a call to an address with a specific msg.value, with specified revert data.
 663 |     |     function mockCallRevert(address callee, uint256 msgValue, bytes calldata data, bytes calldata revertData)
 664 |     |         external;
 665 |     | 
 666 |     |     // --- Impersonation (pranks) ---
 667 |     | 
 668 |     |     // Sets the *next* call's msg.sender to be the input address
 669 |     |     function prank(address msgSender) external;
 670 |     | 
 671 |     |     // Sets all subsequent calls' msg.sender to be the input address until `stopPrank` is called
 672 |     |     function startPrank(address msgSender) external;
 673 |     | 
 674 |     |     // Sets the *next* call's msg.sender to be the input address, and the tx.origin to be the second input
 675 |     |     function prank(address msgSender, address txOrigin) external;
 676 |     | 
 677 |     |     // Sets all subsequent calls' msg.sender to be the input address until `stopPrank` is called, and the tx.origin to be the second input
 678 |     |     function startPrank(address msgSender, address txOrigin) external;
 679 |     | 
 680 |     |     // Resets subsequent calls' msg.sender to be `address(this)`
 681 |     |     function stopPrank() external;
 682 |     | 
 683 |     |     // Reads the current `msg.sender` and `tx.origin` from state and reports if there is any active caller modification
 684 |     |     function readCallers() external returns (CallerMode callerMode, address msgSender, address txOrigin);
 685 |     | 
 686 |     |     // -------- State Snapshots --------
 687 |     | 
 688 |     |     // Snapshot the current state of the evm.
 689 |     |     // Returns the id of the snapshot that was created.
 690 |     |     // To revert a snapshot use `revertTo`
 691 |     |     function snapshot() external returns (uint256 snapshotId);
 692 |     | 
 693 |     |     // Revert the state of the EVM to a previous snapshot
 694 |     |     // Takes the snapshot id to revert to.
 695 |     |     // Returns true if the revert succeeded, false otherwise.
 696 |     |     //
 697 |     |     // This does not automatically delete the snapshot. To delete the snapshot use `deleteSnapshot` or `revertToAndDelete`
 698 |     |     function revertTo(uint256 snapshotId) external returns (bool success);
 699 |     | 
 700 |     |     // Deletes the snapshot.
 701 |     |     // Returns true if the snapshot existed, false otherwise.
 702 |     |     //
 703 |     |     // This does not revert to the state of the snapshot, only deletes it.
 704 |     |     function deleteSnapshot(uint256 snapshotId) external returns (bool success);
 705 |     | 
 706 |     |     // Deletes all snapshots.
 707 |     |     function deleteSnapshots() external;
 708 |     | 
 709 |     |     // Revert the state of the EVM to a previous snapshot
 710 |     |     // Takes the snapshot id to revert to.
 711 |     |     //
 712 |     |     // This also deletes the snapshot after reverting to its state.
 713 |     |     function revertToAndDelete(uint256 snapshotId) external returns (bool success);
 714 |     | 
 715 |     |     // -------- Forking --------
 716 |     |     // --- Creation and Selection ---
 717 |     | 
 718 |     |     // Returns the identifier of the currently active fork. Reverts if no fork is currently active.
 719 |     |     function activeFork() external view returns (uint256 forkId);
 720 |     | 
 721 |     |     // Creates a new fork with the given endpoint and block and returns the identifier of the fork
 722 |     |     function createFork(string calldata urlOrAlias, uint256 blockNumber) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 723 |     | 
 724 |     |     // Creates a new fork with the given endpoint and the _latest_ block and returns the identifier of the fork
 725 |     |     function createFork(string calldata urlOrAlias) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 726 |     | 
 727 |     |     // Creates a new fork with the given endpoint and at the block the given transaction was mined in, replays all transaction mined in the block before the transaction,
 728 |     |     // and returns the identifier of the fork
 729 |     |     function createFork(string calldata urlOrAlias, bytes32 txHash) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 730 |     | 
 731 |     |     // Creates and also selects a new fork with the given endpoint and block and returns the identifier of the fork
 732 |     |     function createSelectFork(string calldata urlOrAlias, uint256 blockNumber) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 733 |     | 
 734 |     |     // Creates and also selects new fork with the given endpoint and at the block the given transaction was mined in, replays all transaction mined in the block before
 735 |     |     // the transaction, returns the identifier of the fork
 736 |     |     function createSelectFork(string calldata urlOrAlias, bytes32 txHash) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 737 |     | 
 738 |     |     // Creates and also selects a new fork with the given endpoint and the latest block and returns the identifier of the fork
 739 |     |     function createSelectFork(string calldata urlOrAlias) external returns (uint256 forkId);
 740 |     | 
 741 |     |     // Updates the currently active fork to given block number
 742 |     |     // This is similar to `roll` but for the currently active fork
 743 |     |     function rollFork(uint256 blockNumber) external;
 744 |     | 
 745 |     |     // Updates the currently active fork to given transaction
 746 |     |     // this will `rollFork` with the number of the block the transaction was mined in and replays all transaction mined before it in the block
 747 |     |     function rollFork(bytes32 txHash) external;
 748 |     | 
 749 |     |     // Updates the given fork to given block number
 750 |     |     function rollFork(uint256 forkId, uint256 blockNumber) external;
 751 |     | 
 752 |     |     // Updates the given fork to block number of the given transaction and replays all transaction mined before it in the block
 753 |     |     function rollFork(uint256 forkId, bytes32 txHash) external;
 754 |     | 
 755 |     |     // Takes a fork identifier created by `createFork` and sets the corresponding forked state as active.
 756 |     |     function selectFork(uint256 forkId) external;
 757 |     | 
 758 |     |     // Fetches the given transaction from the active fork and executes it on the current state
 759 |     |     function transact(bytes32 txHash) external;
 760 |     | 
 761 |     |     // Fetches the given transaction from the given fork and executes it on the current state
 762 |     |     function transact(uint256 forkId, bytes32 txHash) external;
 763 |     |

 765 |     | 
 766 |     |     // In forking mode, explicitly grant the given address cheatcode access
 767 |     |     function allowCheatcodes(address account) external;
 768 |     | 
 769 |     |     // Marks that the account(s) should use persistent storage across fork swaps in a multifork setup
 770 |     |     // Meaning, changes made to the state of this account will be kept when switching forks
 771 |     |     function makePersistent(address account) external;
 772 |     |     function makePersistent(address account0, address account1) external;
 773 |     |     function makePersistent(address account0, address account1, address account2) external;
 774 |     |     function makePersistent(address[] calldata accounts) external;
 775 |     |

 777 |     |     function revokePersistent(address account) external;
 778 |     |     function revokePersistent(address[] calldata accounts) external;
 779 |     | 
 780 |     |     // Returns true if the account is marked as persistent

 785 |     |     // Expects a call to an address with the specified calldata.

 787 |     |     function expectCall(address callee, bytes calldata data) external;
 788 |     |

 793 |     |     function expectCall(address callee, uint256 msgValue, bytes calldata data) external;

 795 |     |     // Expects given number of calls to an address with the specified msg.value and calldata
 796 |     |     function expectCall(address callee, uint256 msgValue, bytes calldata data, uint64 count) external;
 797 |     | 
 798 |     |     // Expect a call to an address with the specified msg.value, gas, and calldata.
 799 |     |     function expectCall(address callee, uint256 msgValue, uint64 gas, bytes calldata data) external;
 800 |     | 
 801 |     |     // Expects given number of calls to an address with the specified msg.value, gas, and calldata.
 802 |     |     function expectCall(address callee, uint256 msgValue, uint64 gas, bytes calldata data, uint64 count) external;
 803 |     | 
 804 |     |     // Expect a call to an address with the specified msg.value and calldata, and a *minimum* amount of gas.
 805 |     |     function expectCallMinGas(address callee, uint256 msgValue, uint64 minGas, bytes calldata data) external;
 806 |     | 
 807 |     |     // Expect given number of calls to an address with the specified msg.value and calldata, and a *minimum* amount of gas.
 808 |     |     function expectCallMinGas(address callee, uint256 msgValue, uint64 minGas, bytes calldata data, uint64 count)
 809 |     |         external;
 810 |     | 
 811 |     |     // Prepare an expected log with (bool checkTopic1, bool checkTopic2, bool checkTopic3, bool checkData).
 812 |     |     // Call this function, then emit an event, then call a function. Internally after the call, we check if
 813 |     |     // logs were emitted in the expected order with the expected topics and data (as specified by the booleans).
 814 |     |     function expectEmit(bool checkTopic1, bool checkTopic2, bool checkTopic3, bool checkData) external;
 815 |     | 
 816 |     |     // Same as the previous method, but also checks supplied address against emitting contract.
 817 |     |     function expectEmit(bool checkTopic1, bool checkTopic2, bool checkTopic3, bool checkData, address emitter)
 818 |     |         external;
 819 |     | 
 820 |     |     // Prepare an expected log with all topic and data checks enabled.
 821 |     |     // Call this function, then emit an event, then call a function. Internally after the call, we check if
 822 |     |     // logs were emitted in the expected order with the expected topics and data.
 823 |     |     function expectEmit() external;
 824 |     | 
 825 |     |     // Same as the previous method, but also checks supplied address against emitting contract.
 826 |     |     function expectEmit(address emitter) external;
 827 |     | 
 828 |     |     // Expects an error on next call that exactly matches the revert data.
 829 |     |     function expectRevert(bytes calldata revertData) external;
 830 |     | 
 831 |     |     // Expects an error on next call that starts with the revert data.
 832 |     |     function expectRevert(bytes4 revertData) external;
 833 |     | 
 834 |     |     // Expects an error on next call with any revert data.
 835 |     |     function expectRevert() external;
 836 |     | 
 837 |     |     // Only allows memory writes to offsets [0x00, 0x60)  [min, max) in the current subcontext. If any other
 838 |     |     // memory is written to, the test will fail. Can be called multiple times to add more ranges to the set.
 839 |     |     function expectSafeMemory(uint64 min, uint64 max) external;
 840 |     | 
 841 |     |     // Only allows memory writes to offsets [0x00, 0x60)  [min, max) in the next created subcontext.
 842 |     |     // If any other memory is written to, the test will fail. Can be called multiple times to add more ranges
 843 |     |     // to the set.
 844 |     |     function expectSafeMemoryCall(uint64 min, uint64 max) external;
 845 |     | 
 846 |     |     // Marks a test as skipped. Must be called at the top of the test.
 847 |     |     function skip(bool skipTest) external;

    1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
    2 |     | pragma solidity >=0.4.22 <0.9.0;
    3 |     | 
    4 |     | library console {
    5 |     |     address constant CONSOLE_ADDRESS = address(0x000000000000000000636F6e736F6c652e6c6f67);
    6 |     | 
    7 |     |     function _sendLogPayload(bytes memory payload) private view {
    8 |     |         uint256 payloadLength = payload.length;
    9 |     |         address consoleAddress = CONSOLE_ADDRESS;
   10 |     |         /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
   11 |     |         assembly {
   12 |     |             let payloadStart := add(payload, 32)
   13 |     |             let r := staticcall(gas(), consoleAddress, payloadStart, payloadLength, 0, 0)
   14 |     |         }
   15 |     |     }
   16 |     | 
   17 |     |     function log() internal view {
   18 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log()"));
   19 |     |     }
   20 |     | 
   21 |     |     function logInt(int p0) internal view {
   22 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(int)", p0));
   23 |     |     }
   24 |     |

   26 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(uint)", p0));
   27 |     |     }

/Users/elvisskozdopolj/Documents/TOB/echidna-auto-poc/test/lib/forge-std/src/console2.sol
    1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
    2 |     | pragma solidity >=0.4.22 <0.9.0;
    3 |     | 
    4 |     | /// @dev The original console.sol uses `int` and `uint` for computing function selectors, but it should
    5 |     | /// use `int256` and `uint256`. This modified version fixes that. This version is recommended
    6 |     | /// over `console.sol` if you don't need compatibility with Hardhat as the logs will show up in
    7 |     | /// forge stack traces. If you do need compatibility with Hardhat, you must use `console.sol`.
    8 |     | /// Reference: https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/2178
    9 |     | library console2 {
   10 |     |     address constant CONSOLE_ADDRESS = address(0x000000000000000000636F6e736F6c652e6c6f67);
   11 |     | 
   12 |     |     function _castLogPayloadViewToPure(
   13 |     |         function(bytes memory) internal view fnIn
   14 |     |     ) internal pure returns (function(bytes memory) internal pure fnOut) {
   15 |     |         assembly {
   16 |     |             fnOut := fnIn
   17 |     |         }
   18 |     |     }
   19 |     | 
   20 |     |     function _sendLogPayload(bytes memory payload) internal pure {
   21 |     |         _castLogPayloadViewToPure(_sendLogPayloadView)(payload);
   22 |     |     }
   23 |     | 
   24 |     |     function _sendLogPayloadView(bytes memory payload) private view {
   25 |     |         uint256 payloadLength = payload.length;
   26 |     |         address consoleAddress = CONSOLE_ADDRESS;
   27 |     |         /// @solidity memory-safe-assembly
   28 |     |         assembly {
   29 |     |             let payloadStart := add(payload, 32)
   30 |     |             let r := staticcall(gas(), consoleAddress, payloadStart, payloadLength, 0, 0)
   31 |     |         }
   32 |     |     }
   33 |     | 
   34 |     |     function log() internal pure {
   35 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log()"));
   36 |     |     }
   37 |     | 
   38 |     |     function logInt(int256 p0) internal pure {
   39 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(int256)", p0));
   40 |     |     }
   41 |     | 
   42 |     |     function logUint(uint256 p0) internal pure {
   43 |     |         _sendLogPayload(abi.encodeWithSignature("log(uint256)", p0));
   44 |     |     }
   45 |     |

  1 |     | // SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
  2 |     | pragma solidity >=0.6.2 <0.9.0;
  3 |     | 
  4 |     | pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;
  5 |     | 
  6 |     | interface IMulticall3 {
  7 |     |     struct Call {
  8 |     |         address target;
  9 |     |         bytes callData;
 10 |     |     }
 11 |     | 
 12 |     |     struct Call3 {
 13 |     |         address target;
 14 |     |         bool allowFailure;
 15 |     |         bytes callData;
 16 |     |     }
 17 |     | 
 18 |     |     struct Call3Value {
 19 |     |         address target;
 20 |     |         bool allowFailure;
 21 |     |         uint256 value;
 22 |     |         bytes callData;
 23 |     |     }
 24 |     | 
 25 |     |     struct Result {
 26 |     |         bool success;
 27 |     |         bytes returnData;
 28 |     |     }
 29 |     | 
 30 |     |     function aggregate(Call[] calldata calls)
 31 |     |         external
 32 |     |         payable
 33 |     |         returns (uint256 blockNumber, bytes[] memory returnData);
 34 |     | 
 35 |     |     function aggregate3(Call3[] calldata calls) external payable returns (Result[] memory returnData);
 36 |     | 
 37 |     |     function aggregate3Value(Call3Value[] calldata calls) external payable returns (Result[] memory returnData);
 38 |     | 
 39 |     |     function blockAndAggregate(Call[] calldata calls)
 40 |     |         external
 41 |     |         payable
 42 |     |         returns (uint256 blockNumber, bytes32 blockHash, Result[] memory returnData);
 43 |     | 
 44 |     |     function getBasefee() external view returns (uint256 basefee);
 45 |     | 
 46 |     |     function getBlockHash(uint256 blockNumber) external view returns (bytes32 blockHash);
 47 |     | 
 48 |     |     function getBlockNumber() external view returns (uint256 blockNumber);
 49 |     | 
 50 |     |     function getChainId() external view returns (uint256 chainid);
 51 |     | 
 52 |     |     function getCurrentBlockCoinbase() external view returns (address coinbase);
 53 |     | 
 54 |     |     function getCurrentBlockDifficulty() external view returns (uint256 difficulty);
 55 |     | 
 56 |     |     function getCurrentBlockGasLimit() external view returns (uint256 gaslimit);
 57 |     | 
 58 |     |     function getCurrentBlockTimestamp() external view returns (uint256 timestamp);
 59 |     | 
 60 |     |     function getEthBalance(address addr) external view returns (uint256 balance);
 61 |     | 
 62 |     |     function getLastBlockHash() external view returns (bytes32 blockHash);
 63 |     | 
 64 |     |     function tryAggregate(bool requireSuccess, Call[] calldata calls)
 65 |     |         external
 66 |     |         payable
 67 |     |         returns (Result[] memory returnData);
 68 |     | 
 69 |     |     function tryBlockAndAggregate(bool requireSuccess, Call[] calldata calls)
